.sp 0


.SS
var v1 = var.dump();
.PP
Return a string describing internal data of a var.
.sp 0
.PP
If the var holds an internal std::string using heap storage then its its heap storage address is given.
.sp 0
.PP
\fBtyp:\fR Multiple typs may exist simultaneously.
.sp 0
.PD 0 \"<dl>
.TP 10\"<dt>
\fB0x01\fR \"</dt>
str is available.
.\"</dd>
.TP 10\"<dt>
\fB0x02\fR \"</dt>
int is available.
.\"</dd>
.TP 10\"<dt>
\fB0x04\fR \"</dt>
dbl is available.
.\"</dd>
.TP 10\"<dt>
\fB0x08\fR \"</dt>
nan: str is not a number.
.\"</dd>
